-- Czech Republic Leads Italy in Fed Cup Semis; Russia, Serbia Tied
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-04-21T17:20:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-21/czech-republic-leads-italy-in-fed-cup-semis-russia-serbia-tied.html
The  Czech Republic  leads Italy 2-0
after the opening day of the Fed Cup tennis semifinals, while
 Russia  and Serbia are tied 1-1.  Lucie Safarova put the defending champion Czechs in front
in Ostrava by beating Francesca Schiavone 7-6 (7-3), 6-1, before
Wimbledon champion Petra Kvitova defeated Sara Errani 6-4, 6-3.  Two-time Grand Slam winner Svetlana Kuznetsova beat Anna
Ivanovic 6-2, 2-6, 6-4 to pull Russia into the tie with Serbia
in Moscow. The visitors won the first match as Jelena Jankovic
defeated Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova 6-4, 6-3.  The semifinals conclude tomorrow with two reverse singles
matches and a doubles match. The winners advance to final of
women’s tennis’s elite team competition in November.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  